00:00:00.950 --> 00:00:05.009
Heather Nicholds: Hey guys this is Heather
from healthy eating starts here. Now sprouts

00:00:05.009 --> 00:00:11.500
are amazing, they have a ton of nutrition
in them, but they are only useful if you actually

00:00:11.500 --> 00:00:16.640
eat them. And a lot of people will buy or
grow sprouts and then have no idea what to

00:00:16.640 --> 00:00:17.640
do with them.

00:00:17.640 --> 00:00:23.020
So the easiest thing to do with sprouts is
to put them in a smoothie. All you do is blend

00:00:23.020 --> 00:00:29.240
them up with some fruits, whatever else you
like and those sprouts will blend up and mix

00:00:29.240 --> 00:00:32.180
in and you’ll barely even notice them.

00:00:32.180 --> 00:00:38.120
So what I am going to show is a very simple
smoothie that I make on a very regular basis

00:00:38.120 --> 00:00:46.000
and it uses a ton of sprouts. So all you do
is get a blender and I like to use frozen

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:52.450
bananas, so I just have a bag of bananas in
my freezer that I keep in there for making

00:00:52.450 --> 00:00:54.060
smoothies.

00:00:54.060 --> 00:00:57.930
And then what happens is I can buy a big bunch
of bananas, let them get ripe, peel them;

00:00:57.930 --> 00:01:03.680
stick them in the freezer, all ready to go
for smoothies. And then I have some frozen

00:01:03.680 --> 00:01:10.889
berries as well. I really like blueberries
in smoothies, although any type of berry you

00:01:10.889 --> 00:01:17.299
want to use is fantastic, raspberries, blackberries,
strawberries whatever you like. There is also

00:01:17.299 --> 00:01:22.929
frozen mango, frozen cherries, all that stuff
is fantastic, okay.

00:01:22.929 --> 00:01:29.340
So that’s my fruit base and then I am also
going to put in some fresh ginger. I love

00:01:29.340 --> 00:01:35.929
ginger, it is warming, so in the winter if
you are having smoothies it can be kind of

00:01:35.929 --> 00:01:41.710
cooling and ginger can help offset that. Another
thing is in the summer I love having smoothies

00:01:41.710 --> 00:01:47.529
for breakfast but in the winter it gets a
little cold in the morning so I usually have

00:01:47.529 --> 00:01:53.609
them in the afternoon which is when I am the
warmest and when the temperature tends to

00:01:53.609 --> 00:01:54.609
be the warmest.

00:01:54.609 --> 00:02:00.619
So I am just cutting the skin off of that
ginger and cutting it into little chunks so

00:02:00.619 --> 00:02:07.770
that it blends up nicely. Put those in the
blender along with some sprouts. So I have

00:02:07.770 --> 00:02:16.120
a large bunch here and I am going to use about
half of this because I love sprouts, but you

00:02:16.120 --> 00:02:18.950
can use however much you want.

00:02:18.950 --> 00:02:25.569
As a little side note, alfalfa sprouts, which
I am using today, fantastic! But, not fantastic

00:02:25.569 --> 00:02:32.070
for everybody. They can aggravate arthritis
and joint inflammation for some people. So

00:02:32.070 --> 00:02:37.879
an easy alternative is to use red clover sprouts.
They are just as easy to make and I have a

00:02:37.879 --> 00:02:42.189
video on how to grow your own sprouts that
you can check out for more info on that.

00:02:42.189 --> 00:02:47.860
And these kinds of things, healthy foods that
may not be good for everyone is something

